Nomura shares hit new high for 1997 . Shares in Nomura Securities Co Ltd hit a new high for this calendar year on Friday , as relieved investors returned to buy the shares after long - awaited administrative penalties for its role in a racketeer scandal were finally announced on Wednesday , traders said . At 0147 GMT , the share price was up 60 yen at 1 , 740 yen , a new high for 1997 , making the brokerage the fourth - largest percentage gainer on the first section of the Tokyo bourse . Brokers said bargain - hunting continued to lift the shares , as the penalties announced on Wednesday were within market expectations and market participants believed that all the negative factors related to the racketeer scandal were now out in the open . 
